column5: Started dipsy's diving around 6:45am ,spent about four hours doing that.Marked tons of fish all day in the 40-50' range. A couple hits and a nice Perch in 53' of water for myself lol. Shaun(xx goaler) and I decided let's jig in a area we found which was almost constant beeps and fish throughout the column. I start at the bottom,him at 40',I'm in 121'.and he gets a hit. A real nice and respectable 9lb laker for table fare.Nice job bud!!

If you look way back behind him,you will see Terry and I floating about. i knew we seen you out there.LMAO  Nice fish and eater Dave.  We marked lots today as well,but hard to hold on them in a toon with stupid crazy current.  Well done byes.
\great job of netting Daveybouy, Thanks for the great day
Nice fish there Daveybouyâ€¦.must get me a smoker next year.
Great Job Davey Buoy!!  Lakers are so beautiful!
that makes for a good day on the water  - keep working those dipseys - they take a while to zone in, but once you get them figured out they are very productive
